          "body": "A few minor changes to wording.",
          "createdAt": "2025-02-20T13:51:34Z",
          "updatedAt": "2025-02-20T13:53:06Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 32,
              "body": "I think we can say \"RDNM is designed to deliver traditional FCAPS capabilities.\", designed probably better word than aimed.",
              "createdAt": "2025-02-20T13:51:34Z",
              "updatedAt": "2025-02-20T13:53:06Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 39,
              "body": "\"Some extensions, which are generic for all network layers, will be defined in the RDNM extension models, including the generic TE topology RDNM extension and the generic TE tunnel RDNM extension. Layer-specific RDNM extensions can be found in other YANG data modules.\"",
              "createdAt": "2025-02-20T13:52:00Z",
              "updatedAt": "2025-02-20T13:53:06Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 61,
              "body": "\"Traditional transport standards do not include a concept of TE-related modeling. If we aim to extend the current IETF data models for a comprehensive representation of the traditional approach, referred to as the RDNM extension. We propose defining common attributes for all technologies within a TE topology RDNM extension model.\"",
              "createdAt": "2025-02-20T13:52:41Z",
              "updatedAt": "2025-02-20T13:53:06Z"
            }
          ]
        },
